{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blog/xue-hua-piao-piao","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I did a cover version of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Spray_of_Plum_Blossoms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><em>A Spray of Plum Blossoms</em></a> (<em>一剪梅</em>), which is perhaps better known as <a href=\"https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=xue%20hua%20piao%20piao%20bei%20feng%20xiao%20xiao\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Xue Hua Piao Piao Bei Feng Xiao Xiao</a>.</p>\n<p><iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/CsuBcQ8uACo?rel=0\" frameBorder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowFullScreen></iframe></p>\n<h2 id=\"motivation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#motivation\" aria-label=\"motivation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Motivation</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>This oldie Chinese song has become really trending in English-speaking countries, so I thought it’d be cool to cover it in my own way.</li>\n<li>My dad is a big fan of the original singer of the song and enjoys singing this song a lot. I thought it would be really cool to cover this song and show it to him.</li>\n<li>I just started to learn DAW (digital audio workstation), so doing a cover is also a great opportunity for me to learn DAW.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"concept\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#concept\" aria-label=\"concept permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Concept</h2>\n<p>I use this virtual singer called <a href=\"https://synthv.fandom.com/wiki/AiKO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">AiKO</a>, who is basically the same as <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hatsune_Miku\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Hatsune Miku</a> (初音) except that AiKO sings in Chinese. I bought the <a href=\"https://www.anicute.com/product/8d45e4f7-58c7-455f-b0ab-d280524021f1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">AiKO sound library</a> for USD $60.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3f8941aab51f42329f3e78352b06cda5/8ec4b/aiko.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 142.33128834355827%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"AiKO\"\n        title=\"AiKO\"\n        src=\"/static/3f8941aab51f42329f3e78352b06cda5/a6d36/aiko.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3f8941aab51f42329f3e78352b06cda5/222b7/aiko.png 163w,\n/static/3f8941aab51f42329f3e78352b06cda5/ff46a/aiko.png 325w,\n/static/3f8941aab51f42329f3e78352b06cda5/a6d36/aiko.png 650w,\n/static/3f8941aab51f42329f3e78352b06cda5/e548f/aiko.png 975w,\n/static/3f8941aab51f42329f3e78352b06cda5/3c492/aiko.png 1300w,\n/static/3f8941aab51f42329f3e78352b06cda5/8ec4b/aiko.png 6378w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I did some rap in this song to add more color to this song. The rap lyrics is basically just rearranged lyrics of the original lyrics.</p>\n<p>My wife recommended me to feature our daughter Valentina, who is 4 years old, in this song. I thought that’s a really good idea, so I did it! In this cover song, you can also hear my daughter “rap” the signature phrase “Xue Hua Piao Piao Bei Feng Xiao Xiao” throughout the song. It’s pretty fun!</p>\n<h2 id=\"production\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#production\" aria-label=\"production permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Production</h2>\n<p>Here is a brief summary of how I produced this song.</p>\n<h3 id=\"music\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#music\" aria-label=\"music permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Music</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Get a <a href=\"https://www.midishow.com/tool/mididy?id=42526\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">instrument MIDI</a> online and import it to my DAW — Logic Pro.</li>\n<li>Speed up the tempo (70 bpm => 90 bpm) and change and the key (A♭m => E♭m).</li>\n<li>Edit the drum track as the original drum is too busy for my taste.</li>\n<li>Export the melody instrument MIDI track and import it to <a href=\"https://dreamtonics.com/synthesizerv-gen1/en/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Synthesizer V</a>.</li>\n<li>Load up <a href=\"https://www.anicute.com/product/8d45e4f7-58c7-455f-b0ab-d280524021f1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">AiKO sound library</a> in Synthesizer V, and enter the lyrics.</li>\n<li>Create vibrato with Synthesizer V pitch editor. Vibrato is used a lot in this song.</li>\n<li>Render the AiKO’s vocal to an audio file (<code class=\"language-text\">.wav</code> file) and import it to Logic Pro.</li>\n<li>Record my rap and my dauther’s rap and add them to the project.</li>\n<li>Add effects like reverb, EQ, and compression.</li>\n<li>Finally, bounce all the tracks in Logic Pro into one <code class=\"language-text\">.mp3</code> file.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"video\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#video\" aria-label=\"video permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Video</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Import the <code class=\"language-text\">.mp3</code> audio file to Final Cut Pro.</li>\n<li>Import background images (the snow photo is from <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">upsplash</a>).</li>\n<li>Enter lyrics and credits.</li>\n<li>Finally, export the music video!</li>\n</ol>","frontmatter":{"date":"July 13, 2020","slug":"/blog/xue-hua-piao-piao","title":"Xue Hua Piao Piao"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/xue-hua-piao-piao"}}}